<p>FRIDAY, April 24th. <lb/></p> 

<p>On the opening of the Assembly to<lb break="no"/>day Premier Haultain moved that the <lb/>
House resolve itself into committee to <lb/>
consider the Supply to be granted to <lb/>
His Honor the Lieutenant Governor. <lb/>
A message from His Honor was re<lb break="no"/>ceived submitting an estimate of $100,-<lb break="maybe"/>000. In making the motion the Pre<lb break="no"/>mier said the government must be car<lb break="no"/>ried on until the final passage of the <lb/>
